label.value: decreased protein level in anaphase-promoting complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the anaphase-promoting complex is lower than normal.

definition.value: Use this term for cases where the relative abundance of one or more specific proteins in the anaphase-promoting complex is decreased, altering the anaphase-promoting complex stoichiometry. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased level of hexose transport gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more hexose transport RNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Hexose transport RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in transport of six-carbon sugars.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: decreased histone H4 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H4 acetylation occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K5 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 5 of histone H4 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K8 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 8 of histone H4 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K12 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal rRNA modification

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which rRNA modification, the covalent alteration of one or more nucleotides within an rRNA molecule, is abnormal.

label.value: abolished 18S rRNA acetylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the posttranscriptional addition of acetyl groups to residues in an 18S rRNA molecule is abolished.

definition.value: At present, the C1297 and C1815 residues are known to be acetylated.

label.value: abnormal ribosome biogenesis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which ribosome biogenesis is abnormal.

label.value: decreased double-stranded DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of double-stranded DNA binding by a gene product is decreased, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: normal duration of septum assembly

value.value: A cell cycle phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of septum assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal duration of actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of actomyosin contractile ring contraction is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Contractile ring contraction is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring constricts.

label.value: decreased duration of protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein is localized to the actomyosin contractile ring for a shorter time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable elongated septated mononucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell is inviable, contains one nucleus and one or more septa and is elongated. Cells with this phenotype are inviable, and the nucleus is not in the normal location.

definition.value: In cells with this phenotype, septation has proceeded despite chromosome segregation failing to complete normally. Chromosome segregation may be incomplete or entirely abolished. Consider also annotating to 'cut' (FYPO:0003155), 'septation following abnormal chromosome segregation, with binucleate and anucleate compartment formation' (FYPO:0003166), or their descendants, because these phenotypes often co-occur.

label.value: abnormal mitotic sister chromatid arm separation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid separation is abnormal along the chromosome arms. Mitotic sister chromatid separation is the process in which sister chromatids are physically detached from each other during mitosis.

label.value: abolished mitotic chromosome centromere condensation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic chromosome condensation does not occur in centromeric regions (i.e. adjacent to the kinetochores).

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at chromosome arms

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is increased along the chromosome arms.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, swollen binucleate multiseptate cell with central constriction

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, has a larger diameter and volume than normal, contains two nuclei and more than one septum, and has an abnormal shape featuring a constriction at the center of the cell, corresponding to the cell division site. In some such cells, the diameter at the ends is much greater than in wild-type cells.

label.value: decreased H4-K20 dimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased gamma-tubulin complex localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of the gamma-tubulin complex to the spindle pole body is decreased.

label.value: increased ribonucleotide incorporation on leading strand

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which more ribonucleotides than normal are incorporated into the leading strand during mitotic DNA replication.

label.value: increased ribonucleotide incorporation on lagging strand

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which more ribonucleotides than normal are incorporated into the lagging strand during mitotic DNA replication.

label.value: normal mutation rate

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mutations occur at a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) frequency.

label.value: abnormal protein phosphorylation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abnormal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein phosphorylation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 5 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: abolished phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II does not occur when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II occurs to a greater extent than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to kinetochore

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to UV

value.value: A gene expression phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of translation in response to ultraviolet light is abnormal.

label.value: translation regulation phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A gene expression phenotype that affects the regulation of translation in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal mitotic sister chromatid segregation with lagging chromosomes and decreased rate of mitotic spindle elongation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic spindle elongation is decreased, and sister chromatids do not move towards the spindle poles at the same time during mitosis prior to completion of chromosome segregation.

label.value: abnormal mitotic sister chromatid segregation with lagging chromosomes, complete sister chromatid separation, and decreased rate of mitotic spindle elongation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic spindle elongation is decreased, and sister chromatids do not move towards the spindle poles at the same time during mitosis prior to completion of chromosome segregation. Although one or more chromosomes remain distant from the spindle pole after the bulk of the DNA has separated, mitotic sister chromatid segregation does eventually go on to complete separation of chromosomes.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoter during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoters is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoter during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoters is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoter during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at RNA polymerase II promoters is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased chromatin binding during cellular response to nitrogen starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at RNA polymerase II-regulated genes during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to regions of chromatin containing genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal RITS complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RITS complex assembly is abnormal.

label.value: normal cell cycle regulation during cellular response to latrunculin A

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the regulation of the mitotic cell cycle in response to latrunculin A is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Normally, cell cycle progression is slowed or arrested transiently following exposure to latrunculin A.

label.value: binucleate multiseptate cell, septa grouped

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell has two and more than one septum, and the septa are grouped together between the two compartments, one or more of which may contain multiple nuclei.

label.value: abolished meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping does not occur. Meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping is the process by which SPO11/Rec12-oligonucleotide complexes are removed from 5' DNA double-strand breaks induced during meiosis.

label.value: decreased meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping is decreased. Meiotic DNA double-strand break clipping is the process by which SPO11/Rec12-oligonucleotide complexes are removed from 5' DNA double-strand breaks induced during meiosis.

label.value: decreased meiotic DNA double-strand break resection

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic DNA double-strand break resection is decreased. Meiotic DNA double-strand break resection is the process by which long-tract single-stranded 3'-end DNA is generated by removal of bases from a 5' end from which SPO11/Rec12-oligonucleotide complexes have been removed.

label.value: normal meiotic DNA double-strand break resection

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic DNA double-strand break resection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Meiotic DNA double-strand break resection is the process by which long-tract single-stranded 3'-end DNA is generated by removal of bases from a 5' end from which SPO11/Rec12-oligonucleotide complexes have been removed.
